<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-07T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/12–746: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in India</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <gloss target="#t_Niact1"><hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi></gloss></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-07T13:00:00-05:00">December 7, 1946—1
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>912. Brit Govt has told us through Brit Emb here it believes it might
                                be helpful if we expressed informally to Congress leaders,
                                particularly Nehru, views this Govt as indicated last two paragraphs
                                    <pb facs="0119" n="101" xml:id="pg_101"/>
                                <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 893 Nov 30 to you.<note n="55" xml:id="d62fn55">Same as telegram 7979 to London, <ref target="#pg_97">p. 97</ref>.</note> Upon arrival Nehru New
                                Delhi and prior meeting Congress Working Committee tomorrow night,
                                please emphasize to him views this Govt as expressed aforementioned
                                telegram.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>